We can implement our own set of math functions under the namespace mxnet::math. For example
```
namespace mxnet {
namespace math {
template<typename DType>
DType exp(DType value);

template<>
double exp(double value);

}
}

@humdings @twiecki how would you thread those additional arguments to `get_symbol_rets`.  The whole point of this function is that it's being called behind the scenes by `create_*_tearsheet` with a symbol.  If you wanted to forward arguments, then all the tearsheet functions would need to accept additional args and kwargs, at which point you might as well just load the benchmark explicitly as an array and pass it in.

If your symbol returns function needs database credentials, it can close over them like this:

```
creds = get_db_credentials()
connection = DatabaseConnection(creds)

def my_benchmark_func(symbol):
    return connection.make_some_query(...)
```

This is also a perfectly good use-case for `functools.partial`.

